OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778652345
OL,3,CSome of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,4,Ccontain 'alarmingly high' levels of
OL,5,Csalt
OL,7,FThere were also "clear examples of
OL,8,Fcompanies getting it right", including
OL,9,Fevery product surveyed from Pollen +
OL,10,FGrace, The Gym Kitchen, and Urban
OL,11,FRajah, which all met calorie and salt
OL,12,Freduction targets, had no red warning
OL,13,Flabels on front of pack, and none of
OL,14,Ftheir sandwiches were classed as high
OL,15,Fin fat, sugar or salt (HFSS).
OL,26,@oD@QOUpD@[O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778652345
OL,3,CSome of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,4,Ccontain 'alarmingly high' levels of
OL,5,Csalt
OL,7,FAmong retailers, Asda and Lidl
OL,8,Fachieved full compliance to the salt
OL,9,Ftargets for sandwiches, and Starbucks
OL,10,Fand Greggs provided the lowest average
OL,11,Fsalt levels in the OOH sector, with
OL,12,Ffull compliance with the salt and
OL,13,Fcalorie targets.
OL,15,FStudies suggest that UK adults consume
OL,16,F8.4g of salt a day on average, 40%
OL,17,Fabove the maximum limit, with much of
OL,18,Fit hidden in processed, pre-packed and
OL,19,Fout-of-home foods such as sandwiches.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778652345
OL,3,CSome of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,4,Ccontain 'alarmingly high' levels of
OL,5,Csalt
OL,7,FToo much salt raises blood pressure, a
OL,8,Fleading cause of stroke and a major
OL,9,Fdriver of heart and kidney disease.
OL,11,FConsumers buy 11.5 billion sandwiches
OL,12,Facross the UK every year.
OL,14,FSonia Pombo, head of research and
OL,15,Fimpact at Action on Salt & Sugar,
OL,16,Fsaid: "Most people choose sandwiches
OL,17,Ffor lunch for their simplicity,
OL,18,Fconvenience and affordability. But
OL,19,Fwhat they're actually eating can be a
OL,20,Ffull day's worth of salt hidden
OL,21,Fbetween two slices of bread.
OL,26,@xD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G12/13
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,308,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1778652345
OL,3,CSome of UK's most popular sandwiches
OL,4,Ccontain 'alarmingly high' levels of
OL,5,Csalt
OL,7,F"More than 20 years after the first
OL,8,Fset of salt reduction targets were
OL,9,Fintroduced, it's frankly unacceptable
OL,10,Fthat some companies continue to sell
OL,11,Fsandwiches that exceed an adult's
OL,12,Fdaily limit in one go.
OL,14,F"Voluntary action has been allowed to
OL,15,Fdrift for too long, and the result is
OL,16,Fa food environment that continues to
OL,17,Fput public health at risk. The
OL,18,FGovernment must now step in with
OL,19,Ftough, mandatory measures, because
OL,20,Fleaving this to industry goodwill has
OL,21,Fclearly failed."
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@AOU}D@PO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G13/13
